list.abstract: Tag在中国并没有统一的中文名称，有的称之为“分类”，也有的称之为“开放分类”或“大众分类”，还有的称之为“标签”。Tag（标签）是一种更为灵活、有趣的日志分类方式，可以为每篇日志添加一个或多个Tag（标签），然后可以看到BlogBus上所有和您使用了相同Tag的日志，并且由此和其他用户产生更多的联系和沟通。
TAG，韩国男团Ciipher成员。 2022年5月11日，随组合发行专辑《THE CODE》。

yingyinNormal.en: What tag? There's a tag on my fin! How could you forget you have a tag on your fin?
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么标签？我的鳍上有标签？你怎么会忘记你的鳍上有标签？

yingyinNormal.en: I just want to live in a glass box alone. That's all I want. So give me your tag! Hey, man, don't touch my tag!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只想单独住在玻璃箱里，如此而已，标签给我吧。拜托，别碰我的标签！

yingyinNormal.en: No, no, no. If I just take your tag, I can take your place on the transport truck, then you can go back inside, and find your family. All you have to do is give me the tag.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，要是我戴上你的标签，就能代替你坐上转送卡车，你就能回到里面——找到你爸妈。你把标签给我就行了。

yingyinNormal.en: Not a clue. What were we talking about? You were about to give me your tag.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没印象，我们说了什么？你要把标签交给我。

yingyinNormal.en: But, Hank, I can't go in the pipes alone. I'll forget where I'm going. Not my problem. Tag!
yingyinNormal.zh: 七条郎，我不能自己进水管，我会忘记怎么走。干我屁事，标签！

yingyinNormal.en: There you are! Listen up, you and I are square. I took you to the map, now give me that tag! Wait, wait, wait, no.
yingyinNormal.zh: 找到你了！听好，我们算扯平了，我带你找到地图 ，标签给我！等等，不。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, that's too bad. A deal's a deal. You wanted to find your parents? That's how you get to them. Now give me your tag.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真可惜，但我们说好了，你想要找你的父母？游进去才能找到。把标签给我。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a transport tag for fish who can't cut it inside the institute. They get transferred to permanent digs. An aquarium. In Cleveland.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是把不能适应的鱼送走的标签，被转送到水族馆永久安置。在克里夫兰。

yingyinNormal.en: All right. If I get you to your family will you give me... I don't have much. I... How about if I give you this tag? Great idea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，我带你去找家人，你就会给我……我身上没多少东西，就给你这个标签吧？好主意。

yingyinNormal.en: We used to play tag and stuff.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们常常玩捉迷藏和其他游戏。

yingyinNormal.en: No, you've put an awfully big price tag on this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，是你们开了高额价码。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey. How'd it go? Yeah. What did Tag say? Tag is not the father. And Joey knows now?
yingyinNormal.zh: 情况如何？泰格怎么说？泰格不是孩子的爸，乔伊知道了？

yingyinNormal.en: No way. No way. You just broke up with Tag a week ago.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不行，一星期前你才跟泰格分手。

yingyinNormal.en: You're putting an awfully big price tag on this, Mr. President.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你开的价码有点高啊，总统先生。

yingyinNormal.en: How would you feel about taking out my assistant Tag? I'll pay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你要不要带我的助理泰格出去玩？我付钱。

yingyinNormal.en: Simple. You find him, we tag him. I follow him wherever he goes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很简单，你找到他，我们跟踪他，我会对他紧追不舍。

yingyinNormal.en: How come you didn't have a collar on her? And where's her ID Tag?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为什么不给她戴个项圈? 而且你怎么不给她戴姓名牌?

yingyinNormal.en: Even my mother had an ID Tag on me. Well, it was a flea collar, but...
yingyinNormal.zh: 我妈都给我弄了个带姓名牌的项圈，虽然是除跳蚤用的，但好歹...

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I kind of like my tag. Why do you want it? So I can go to Cleveland.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我蛮喜欢它的，你要它做什么？那样我才能去……我才能去克里夫兰。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. Hey. Hey. So, heard you had some fun with Tag last night. Yeah. That guy's all right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 听说昨晚你跟泰格玩得很开心。对，那家伙还不错。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Since the beginning, this price <highlight>tag</highlight> has been PreCheck's fatal flaw.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从一开始，这个价格标签就是预检的致命缺陷。

examination_example.sentence: 27. The "threatened" <highlight>tag</highlight> disappointed some environmentalists in that it granted less federal regulatory powers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “受威胁”的标签让一些环保主义者失望，因为它授予联邦监管权力较少。

examination_example.sentence: But Ashe and others argued that the "threatened" <highlight>tag</highlight> gave the federal government flexibility to try out new, potentially less confrontational conservation approaches.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但阿什和其他人认为，“受威胁”标签给了联邦政府灵活性，可以尝试新的、可能不那么具有对抗性的保护方法。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指固定在物品上，标明商品的名称、产地和价格等的标签；也可指固定或系在行李等物品上的标签。
指附在物品上，标有物品性质、物主、名称、目的地等的标签。其制作材料为纸、亚麻布、金属、塑料等。

sense_info_list.en: a label attached to someone or something for the purpose of identification or to give other information

examination_example.sentence: In exchange, he guarantees an above-market price for each animal and a calf-to-customer electronic ear <highlight>tag</highlight> ID system like that used in the European Union.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为交换，他保证每只动物的价格都高于市场价，并且提供从小牛到客户的电子耳标 ID 系统（如欧盟使用的系统）。

examination_example.sentence: That includes <highlight>tagging</highlight> the foxes and monitoring their numbers to ensure nothing goes wrong.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这包括标记狐狸并监控狐狸的数量，以确保一切正常。

examination_example.sentence: All of the Spanish birds <highlight>tagged</highlight> in the study flew across the Sahara desert to the western Sahel.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究中标记的所有西班牙鸟类都飞过撒哈拉沙漠到达Sahel西部。

examination_example.sentence: What can be inferred about the Spanish birds <highlight>tagged</highlight> in the study?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于这项研究中标记的西班牙鸟类，可以推断出什么？
